{
  "text": "Cobia is currently raised by at least one producer in the Northeast U.S. and a second in the Southeast U.S. They are commercially produced in Taiwan, Australia, Marshall Islands, Puerto Rico, Bahamas, Belize, Mexico and Brazil as well as several other countries. Thus, much information is available on spawning, egg incubation, larvae culture, temperature tolerance, growth rates [CITATION_1] , feed requirements, and other environmental parameters. Cobia's rapid growth and good feed conversion make it a potential species for production in recirculating systems in the Northeast. The economics of production and marketing of cobia from recirculating systems is not well understood and is an area needing additional research.",
  "citation_candidates": [
